Skipper John O'Shea has challenged Sunderland to keep their fate in their own hands by securing
fifth successive derby victory over Newcastle
The Wear-Tyne rivals meet at the Stadium of Light on Sunday with Sunderland having won the last four meetings
but in grave need of three points to ease themselves away from the developing battle for Barclays Premier League survival
O'Shea and his team-mates could find themselves inside the relegation zone by the time they run out if Burnley get the better of Tottenham in the day 's earlier kick-off
